# Netlify redirects — In the Wake
# Soli Deo Gloria
#
# Ported from .htaccess (issue #1912). Production runs on Netlify, so the
# Apache .htaccess is INERT — its SEO 301s were silently not firing. This
# file restores them. Rules are ordered to match .htaccess (first match wins),
# so runtime behavior matches what Apache would have done.
#
# Every source below was verified PHANTOM (no real file) and every target was
# verified to EXIST on 2026-07-06, so no `!` force flag is needed and no real
# page is shadowed.
#
# DEFERRED (needs operator decision — intentionally NOT ported here):
#   * Security file blocks (.py/.sh/.md/.csv/hidden/backup FilesMatch) and the
#     /scripts/ block: Netlify has no FilesMatch; a clean block needs a 404
#     target page (none exists yet). Better handled by not deploying those
#     files or via a future 404.html + status rule.
#   * /admin/ block: NOT ported. Production pages legitimately link into
#     /admin/ (e.g. the safety article's voyage-pack emergency PDF, family
#     PWAs, trip pages). A blanket block would break live user downloads.
#     Needs an explicit allow-list before any block.
#   * 410-Gone JSON blocks (ships/rcl/assets, videos, travel/articles *.json):
#     skipped — live pages fetch JSON from those paths; blocking risks breakage.
#   * drinks.html, packing.html, ships/carnival/mardi-gras.html: their .htaccess
#     301s were dropped because those are REAL existing files (redirecting them
#     would hide live pages). Left as-is.
#   * ships/carnival/celebration.html: two conflicting .htaccess rules
#     (add "carnival-" prefix vs add "-1987" year). Apache first-match resolves
#     to carnival-celebration.html; that behavior is preserved below, but the
#     ambiguity is flagged for editorial review.
#   * Template-junk patterns (showmenu:, ${slug}, $1, ${url}) and em-dash regex
#     restaurant rules: rely on regex/special chars Netlify _redirects can't
#     express; low value, skipped.

# --- Canonical host: www -> apex (Netlify forces HTTPS automatically) ---
https://www.cruisinginthewake.com/*  https://cruisinginthewake.com/:splat  301!

